    "Hour must be between 0 and 23. You entered {hour}." : "Time skal v\u00e6re mellem 0 og 23. Du indtastede {hour}.",
    "Hours" : "Timer",
    "Hours Today" : "Timer i dag",
    "Hours at a glance" : "Timer p\u00e5 et blik",
    "Hours of rest between end of work and next start. German law requires at least 11 hours." : "Hviletimer mellem arbejdets afslutning og n\u00e6ste start. Tysk lov kr\u00e6ver mindst 11 timer.",
    "Hours paid" : "Timer betalt",
    "How Long to Keep Time Records" : "Hvor l\u00e6nge skal man opbevare tidsregistreringer",
    "How Serious" : "Hvor seri\u00f8st",
    "How it works" : "Hvordan det virker",
    "How many hours of rest someone must have between the end of one work day and the start of the next. German law requires at least 11 hours. Example: If someone finishes work at 6 PM, they cannot start again before 5 AM the next day." : "Hvor mange timers hvile en person skal have mellem slutningen af \u200b\u200ben arbejdsdag og starten af \u200b\u200bden n\u00e6ste. Tysk lov kr\u00e6ver mindst 11 timer. Eksempel: Hvis nogen afslutter arbejdet kl. 18.00, kan de ikke starte igen f\u00f8r kl. 05.00 n\u00e6ste dag.",
    "How many hours you normally work each day. Decimal values are allowed (e.g. 7.74 for a 38.7 h week spread over five days)." : "Hvor mange timer arbejder du normalt hver dag. Decimalv\u00e6rdier er tilladt (f.eks. 7,74 for en uge p\u00e5 38,7 timer fordelt p\u00e5 fem dage).",
    "How many vacation days you get each year. In Germany, the standard is 25 days. Example: Enter 25 if you get 25 vacation days per year." : "Hvor mange feriedage f\u00e5r du hvert \u00e5r. I Tyskland er standarden 25 dage. Eksempel: Indtast 25, hvis du f\u00e5r 25 feriedage om \u00e5ret.",
    "How many years to keep time tracking records before they are automatically deleted. German law typically requires keeping records for 2 years. Example: Enter 2 to keep records for 2 years." : "Hvor mange \u00e5r skal man opbevare tidsregistreringer, f\u00f8r de automatisk slettes. Tysk lov kr\u00e6ver typisk journalf\u00f8ring i 2 \u00e5r. Eksempel: Indtast 2 for at opbevare optegnelser i 2 \u00e5r.",
    "How should annual vacation be calculated?" : "Hvordan skal den \u00e5rlige ferie beregnes?",
    "How the system checked each layer" : "Hvordan systemet kontrollerede hvert lag",
    "How time zones are used" : "Hvordan tidszoner bruges",
    "How times are stored" : "Hvordan tider gemmes",
    "How vacation days are calculated" : "S\u00e5dan beregnes feriedage",
    "How well you follow the rules:" : "Hvor godt f\u00f8lger du reglerne:",
    "How your request is approved" : "Hvordan din anmodning godkendes",
    "How your vacation entitlement is calculated" : "S\u00e5dan beregnes din ferieret",
    "Hypothetical team" : "Hypotetisk hold",
    "Hypothetical team membership" : "Hypotetisk teammedlemskab",
    "I returned early" : "Jeg kom tidligt tilbage",
    "I understand this action cannot be undone" : "Jeg forst\u00e5r, at denne handling ikke kan fortrydes",
    "If a break is left open for too long, the system automatically clocks out to prevent permanent pause status." : "Hvis en pause st\u00e5r \u00e5ben for l\u00e6nge, stemper systemet automatisk ud for at undg\u00e5 permanent pausestatus.",
    "If a calendar month was finalized by mistake or a correction is required, you can reopen it here as an administrator for the employee whose month should be opened again. Use the search field to select that person (their Nextcloud account). You must enter a reason; the audit log records your administrator action, the reason, and who the change applies to. Previous snapshot rows remain in the database for traceability." : "Hvis en kalenderm\u00e5ned er afsluttet ved en fejl, eller der er behov for en rettelse, kan du gen\u00e5bne den her som administrator for den medarbejder, hvis m\u00e5ned skal \u00e5bnes igen. Brug s\u00f8gefeltet til at v\u00e6lge denne person (deres Nextcloud-konto). Du skal indtaste en \u00e5rsag; revisionsloggen registrerer din administratorhandling, \u00e5rsagen og hvem \u00e6ndringen g\u00e6lder for. Tidligere snapshot-r\u00e6kker forbliver i databasen for sporbarhed.",
    "If enabled, users can still turn this reminder off in their personal settings. Reminders are sent only for expected workdays (not weekends, holidays, or approved absences)." : "Hvis den er aktiveret, kan brugere stadig sl\u00e5 denne p\u00e5mindelse fra i deres personlige indstillinger. P\u00e5mindelser sendes kun for forventede arbejdsdage (ikke weekender, helligdage eller godkendt frav\u00e6r).",
    "If enabled: managers are resolved from ArbeitszeitCheck teams defined below. If disabled: managers are resolved from shared Nextcloud groups (default behavior)." : "Hvis aktiveret: ledere l\u00f8ses fra ArbeitszeitCheck-teams defineret nedenfor. Hvis deaktiveret: ledere l\u00f8ses fra delte Nextcloud-grupper (standardadf\u00e6rd).",
    "If set, opening carryover per user cannot exceed this many days (Tarifvertrag / company policy). Leave empty for no cap. Imports and admin edits are clamped to this value." : "Hvis det er indstillet, kan \u00e5bningsoverf\u00f8rsel pr. bruger ikke overstige s\u00e5 mange dage (Tarifvertrag / virksomhedspolitik). Lad v\u00e6re tom for ingen l\u00e5g. Importer og administratorredigeringer er fastgjort til denne v\u00e6rdi.",
    "If set, this date is saved as the overtime \u201cStichtag\u201d when the new account is created. Leave empty to configure later in ArbeitszeitCheck \u2192 Administration \u2192 Employees." : "Hvis den er angivet, gemmes denne dato som overarbejdet \"Stichtag\", n\u00e5r den nye konto oprettes. Lad v\u00e6re tom for at konfigurere senere i ArbeitszeitCheck \u2192 Administration \u2192 Medarbejdere.",
    "If you manage more than one team, you can choose one here." : "Hvis du leder mere end \u00e9t hold, kan du v\u00e6lge et her.",
